cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modeling coherent conversation continuation using RNN-based dialogue models with attention mechanisms. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel approach to improve dialogue generation, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses RNN-based models and attention mechanisms, which are common machine learning techniques. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks for modeling dialogue. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper evaluates the model on dialogue datasets related to movies and troubleshooting, which may involve sound-related aspects.
